{
  "texts": [
    "More specifically, the key decision in our model of social media is made by the platform about the structure of interactions between users.",
    "Users have a political belief (ideology), which they can update according to the information they receive.",
    "This information is contained in social media posts (articles), which come with a specific message (left-wing or right-wing) as well as a degree of reliability (observed perfectly by all players).",
    "Users decide whether to share, ignore or dislike a message, and their main source of utility is from these social media interactions.",
    "Users also vote in a two-party election according to the alignment of their beliefs with the policy positions on offer."
  ]
}